    <p>
        <b>Introduction to the Tool</b><br>
        The “Comprehensive Assessment Tool for Adults with Intellectual Disabilities” (CAT-AID) is a standardized assessment tool for comprehensive evaluation of skills, aptitudes, interests and work-related competencies required for skill training, employability and independent living...
    </p>

    <hr />
    <h4 class="mt-3">Scope / Utility of the Tool</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Useful for adults with Intellectual Disabilities (18+ years) for vocational training and independent living</li>
        <li>Professionals working in vocational rehabilitation</li>
        <li>Employers for job opportunities to adults with Intellectual Disabilities</li>
    </ul>
    <p>When useful: transition stage, vocational assessment, training, placement services.</p>

    <hr />
    <h4 class="mt-3">How the Tool is Used</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>To assess skills, abilities, aptitudes, interests</li>
        <li>To determine occupation suitability</li>
        <li>To facilitate work performance and employment outcomes</li>
        <li>To determine placement decisions</li>
    </ul>

    <hr />
    <h4 class="mt-3">Tool Structure</h4>
    <p>
        <b>PART-A:</b> 8 Domains — Personal Care, Communication, Social-Emotional, Cognitive, Motor, Work Academics, Sex Education, Self-Advocacy <br>
        <b>PART-B:</b> Vocational Aptitude & Workplace Behaviour <br>
        <b>PART-C:</b> SCPwD Job Roles & Job Aids
    </p>

    <hr />
    <p>
        <b>Instructional Guidelines — Assessment Duration:</b> 35 – 50 minutes (Part-A)
    </p>

    <div class="alert alert-info mt-3">
        For complete reference, please consult the official CAT-AID manual.
    </div>
</div>
